1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano",[226,153,227,228,229,230,231,96,232],"Q2SBPG9F","77P5MNIR","2EUC82DH","533T8HNS","D9BZFDDR","9CT5ZWIK","RZSFKACR",[234,235,236,15,19,237,238,239,104,105,239,240,107,75],"isic000964","funerary inscription for agathon",{"_":12},"fine-grained, homogeneous, white marble, likely unspecified. digital microscopy: indistinguishable fabric (identification based on pxrf, digital microscopy)","catina","catania","museo civico di catania","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Ἅπασα γε̑α καὶ πλατοὶς ἀὴρ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>γενᾷ σοι θάνατε \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ἐξαπίνης μου τὸ βρέφος ἥρπασε[ς ἦ] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>τίς ἀνάκη εἰ γὰρ ἐγήρα, οὐχεί σον [ἦν] \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>☧ ἐγενήθη ὁ κύρις Ἀγάθων \u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">π͡ρ\u003C/span>(ὸ) ιε´ ☧ \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>καλανδῶν Νοενβρίων ἡμέρᾳ Κρό[νου] \u003Cbr id=\"al7-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>ἔζη(σεν) \u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">μ͡ῆ\u003C/span>(νας) · ι´ · ἀπέθανε \u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">π͡ρ\u003C/span>(ὸ) · ι´ · [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] καλανδῶν Σεπτενβρ[ίων] \u003Cbr id=\"al8-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">8\u003C/span>ἡμέρᾳ Ἡλίου κυρία Ἀγάθη εἰρήνην Ἀγά[θωνι] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":243,"ptr":244,"ref":245,"inscriptionDate":4,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6,"year":4},"494 no.xv",{"target":112},{"_":114,"target":114},{"file":247,"uri":247,"title":248,"status":249,"editionAuthor":13,"type":251,"objectType":252,"material":256,"condition":28,"layoutDesc":264,"handNote":268,"date":279,"places":281,"geo":284,"country":55,"provenance":193,"provenanceGeo":286,"region":65,"settlement":196,"repository":289,"idno":290,"textLang":292,"tmNumber":294,"facsimile":295,"letterHeights":298,"publications":302,"zotero":305,"keywords":308,"html":313,"bibl":314,"bulletinDateSort":115,"citedRangeSort":315,"languageSort":74,"materialSort":257,"typeSort":15},"ISic001344","Funerary inscription for Agathe",{"_":250},"edited",{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},{"_":253,"ana":254,"ref":255},"lid or cover (of an urn?)","#object.cover","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/84.html",{"_":257,"ana":258,"type":173,"subtype":259,"resp":25,"ref":176},"Fine-grained, homogeneous, white marble, likely Lunense, Docimian, Göktepe, Hymettan. Digital microscopy: homeoblastic fabric (identification based on pXRF, digital microscopy)","#material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Lunense #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Docimian #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Goktepe #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Hymettan",[260,261,262,263],"Lunense","Docimian","Göktepe","Hymettan",{"layout":265},{"p":266,"rs":267,"damage":28},"The text is set out over nine lines, complete apart from the very\n                                        ends of lines 9 and 10. Chi-rho symbols are set to the left of line two and the\n                                        right of line three, and a star is set in the middle between lines one and two.\n                                        There is some crowding in the final two lines. The text is approximately centred\n                                        on the disc and the crowding at the end of line 8 in particular suggests that\n                                        the stone was cut to this circular shape prior to engraving.",{"_":32,"ana":33,"ref":34},{"lettering":269,"dimensions":270},"The letters are neatly but irregularly cut. Lunate epsilon, sigma and\n                                    omega; alpha has a steeply left sloping cross-bar, the right hasta extended well\n                                    above the rest of the letter; beta is tall, with two closed eyes, separated from\n                                    each other. Supralinear lines are used above numerals and also in line 6.",[271,277],{"type":38,"l":272,"from":40,"to":273,"h":274,"unit":41,"atLeast":275,"atMost":276},"Line 1-9","line9","8-21","8","21",{"type":43,"l":278,"from":40,"to":45,"unit":41},"Interlineation not recorded",{"_":280,"notBefore":48,"notAfter":49},"4th or 5th century CE",[282,283],{"_":193,"type":53,"ref":194,"region":55},{"_":196,"type":58,"ref":197,"region":55},[285],[200,201],[287,288],37.503505,15.08893,{"_":204,"role":68,"ref":205},{"_":291,"type":72},"719",{"_":74,"mainLang":75,"languages":293},[74],"492952",{"n":79,"url":296,"height":81,"width":82,"desc":297,"surfaceType":84},"ISic001344_tiled.tif","Photo J.Prag",[299],{"atLeast":300,"atMost":301},8,21,[218,149,219,220,221,303,222,90,304],"Wilhelm, 1909, Beitraege zur griechischen Inschriftenkunde","Ferrua, 1989, Note e giunte alle iscrizioni cristiane antiche della Sicilia",[226,153,227,228,229,306,230,96,307],"5FKDFIPR","759ZXHKQ",[309,310,311,15,253,312,238,239,104,105,239,240,107,75],"isic001344","funerary inscription for agathe",{"_":250},"fine-grained, homogeneous, white marble, likely lunense, docimian, göktepe, hymettan. digital microscopy: homeoblastic fabric (identification based on pxrf, digital microscopy)","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀγάθη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀγάθη\">Ἀγάθη\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span> ☧ ἐτελεύτησεν \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ἐτῶν \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ξ\u003C/span> παρα - ☧\u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span> &lt;σ&gt; κευῇ τε͂ς \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">θ\u003C/span> ἀπὸ κα-\u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>λανδῶν Σεπτεμ-\u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>βρίων · ἐξεκομίσθη \u003Cbr id=\"al7-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>δαὶ Σαββάτοις · \u003Cbr id=\"al8-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">8\u003C/span>χαρίσου τῷ \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Κυρίῳ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κυρίῳ\">Κυρίῳ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al9-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">9\u003C/span>καὶ τῷ \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Χριστῷ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Χριστῷ\">Χριστῷ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.4 reg., orig. τε͂ς | σ | l.6 superscript | superscript\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":315,"ptr":316,"ref":317,"inscriptionDate":4,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6,"year":4},"497 n.85",{"target":112},{"_":114,"target":114},false],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
